The discrete reflexive graph with vertices in a type A, written \mathord {\vartriangle }A, is defined by setting x\approx _{\mathord {\vartriangle }A} y :\equiv  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x = y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 and \mathsf {rx}_{\mathord {\vartriangle }A}{x} :\equiv  \mathsf {refl}.

